metadata.name: Francis' Atheneum
metadata.description:
Francis’ Atheneum is a visual library that houses and displays the support, mentorship, friendship, and brotherhood between Francis Yoo & Wesley Han. In 2008, Francis introduced Wesley to a music creation program called “Fruity Loops Studio”; Wesley’s life was forever changed. Since then he has gone on to create his own music as a producer and releases songs under "Wesley Ruger Han”, “Oogah”, and "Schine". They are a reflection of integrative healing experienced through Francis' guidance using psychoanalytical practices such as Jungian psychology, the Enneagram, and more. 

The soundtrack is a remix of their song "오직 예수" (Ojik Yesu) they co-produced in 2008. In it you hear the deep hums and the Gayageum, a traditional Korean stringed instrument. They are calls to Korean remembrance as the Gayageum dances with the electric guitar as a display of ancient and modern harmony. Their dance symbolizes healing, integration, transformation, and a display of Wesley's past and future in the now.
